# **Predict Future Sales**

Files descriptions

- sales\_train.csv - the training set. Daily historical data from January 2013 to October 2015.
- csv - the test set. You need to forecast the sales for these shops and products for November 2015.
- sample\_submission.csv - a sample submission file in the correct format.
- csv - supplemental information about the items/products.
- item\_categories.csv - supplemental information about the item&#39;s categories.
- csv- supplemental information about the shops.

Data fields

- **ID**  - an Id that represents a (Shop, Item) tuple within the test set
- **shop\_id**  - unique identifier of a shop
- **item\_id**  - unique identifier of a product
- **item\_category\_id**  - unique identifier of item category
- **item\_cnt\_day**  - number of products sold. You are predicting a monthly amount of this measure
- **item\_price**  - current price of an item
- **date**  - date in format dd/mm/yyyy
- **date\_block\_num**  - a consecutive month number, used for convenience. January 2013 is 0, February 2013 is 1,..., October 2015 is 33
- **item\_name**  - name of item
- **shop\_name**  - name of shop
- **item\_category\_name**  - name of item category

We are asking you to predict total sales for every product and store in the next month.

# Experiments and Improvements

We try to change some parameters for better results in ML models:

- In Random forest:

-
  - n\_estimators=50 / 30
  - max\_depth=7 / 3

- In Xgboost:
  - max\_depth = 8
  - n\_estimators= 400 / 100
  - early\_stopping\_rounds = 10
- In linear Regression:
  - We use the results of RF and Xgboost together.
- In Rnn model:

- Adding and removing dense layers.
- Changing the args of dense layers.
- Changing the args of embedding input layer.
- Adding dropout layers.
- Changing the args of dropout layers.
- Using CuDNNLSTM layer.
- We tried 8 different models.
- Epochs = 10, batch size = 4096.

- Concatenation model:
  - Number of input and embedding layers.
  - Number of dense and dropout layers.
  - Epochs = 20, batch size = 4096.

The **split train validation test** method:

1.

- Train: Contain all the data that number of months mod 3 not equals 0.
- Val: Contain all the data that number of months mod 3 equals 0.

1.

- Train: Contain all the data from 7,8,9,12,1,2 months.
- Val: Contain all the data from 10,11 months.

Because the target is month number 11 therefor, we used only the months that close to it.

1.

- Train: Contain all the data from 5,6,7,8,9,12 months.
- Val: Contain all the data from 10,11 months.

Because the target is month number 11 therefor, we used only the months that come before it and one after for similarity.



**Metrices:**

1. Kaggle using MSE therefor we give this method more consideration than MAE.
2. Using graphs to visualize the results for better understanding.
3. Split data by different methods.

# Insights

- When we built the RNN model and use the Embedding layer we saw that input dim of 200 gave us good results but when we change it to 300, we get even better results, we didn&#39;t try to add more because we learn that it should be 100-300.
- We select those features because we get the best score using them:
The idea was to choose the features make the big impact on the product info and time info.

**date\_block\_num        shop\_id        item\_id        item\_cnt\_month        month\_number        item\_category\_id        big\_category\_id        sub\_category\_id        holiday\_month**

- Tried to add &quot;max price per month&quot;, &quot;min price per month&quot; and &quot;diff price&quot; but got higher score (21188), we can see that those have low impact.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Using Embedding layers for each feature gave the same result as Rnn with single Embedding but reduce the overfitting.

- Data split: (best to worst)
  1. Using months: 1,2,7,8,9,12 (month number in calendar) for train and months: 10, 11 for validation.
Because those months close to the month in test (11 in calendar).
  2. Sorting the data by date\_block\_num and split it to by using mod 3
  3. 0-30 months to train and 31-33 months to val.
  4. split it by 80 – 20 presents
- Adding category that contain small number of categories help to improve result
  1. Month number 1-12.
  2. Holiday per days in each month.
  3. Adding category and sub category id.
